The Bank of Portales on Main Street in &lt;a href="Portales%2C%20New%20Mexico"&gt;Portales, New Mexico&lt;/a&gt;, which has also been known as Citizens National Bank;Portales News Tribune Building, was built in 1902 or 1903 and was listed on the &lt;a href="National%20Register%20of%20Historic%20Places"&gt;National Register of Historic Places&lt;/a&gt; in 1984.
It is a two-story commercial building.
A cafe, Do Drop In, is located at 123 S. Main. The &lt;a href="http%3A//focus.nps.gov/GetAsset%3FassetID%3D43e63051-caa5-414b-af87-3705c1803d35"&gt;NRHP nominating form&lt;/a&gt; for the Bank of Portales gives "123 Main", which is either incomplete or incorrect.&lt;/ref&gt;
